# Markdown authoring (project `.md` files)

When editing Markdown in this repository:

1. Bold (`**…**`) — Use only where emphasis is genuinely useful (e.g. a critical warning or a defined term once). Do not sprinkle bold across every label or phrase; it reads noisy and unprofessional.

As a general rule, limit it to one per paragraph, no matter how long the paragraph is.

2. Tables — We recommend using small tables (those with few columns and short cell text). If you have long explanations, facts spanning multiple lines, or a large number of items, use headings or nested bullet points instead. However, since tables are more visually clear than bullet points, please make an effort to use them as long as they meet the above guidelines.

If a table absolutely requires line breaks or has very wide cells, please break it up into sections or bulleted lists.
